ckground:#f0f4f8;border-left:3px solid #7b9fc4;border-radius:3px;font-size:0.82em;color:#444;line-height:1.8;\">💤 <strong>25</strong> · 📝 Q:25 · 🎯 R:25</p>\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/18/becoming-a-british-royal-with-nothing-more-than-confidence-and-an-accent.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Becoming a British royal with nothing more than confidence and an accent\"><img alt=\"Max Fosh with his new son. Image: Max Fosh\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"610\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Max-Fosh-with-his-new-son.-Image-Max-Fosh.jpg?fit=1080%2C610&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1080\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I've said it before, and I'll say it again: <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/tag/max-fosh\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Max Fosh</a> is the only YouTube prankster out there worth a damn. He's not obnoxious, he isn't self-centered, and most rare of all, he doesn't hurt anyone. His workflow begins with isolating a ridiculously silly idea, like <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/24/living-out-your-hollywood-fantasy-by-hiring-stuntmen-to-lose-a-bar-fight.html\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">hiring stuntmen</a> to throw a fight so he can look cool in front of his friends, and doing everything possible to realize it. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/18/becoming-a-british-royal-with-nothing-more-than-confidence-and-an-accent.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/18/becoming-a-british-royal-with-nothing-more-than-confidence-and-an-accent.html\">Becoming a British royal with nothing more than confidence and an accent</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
